Frankly, I think the world sucks. I don't identify with any political group. The alt-right, antifa, ... sharia.. ... conservatism, christianity.... they can go screw themselves, for all I care.
&nbsp;
My only hope is that we can become a spacefaring Type-I civilization, whose only currency is matter and energy. Everybody is free to live the lives they want to live. Nobody can impose their way of life on others. We can all wake up in the morning and smoke weed and listen to Bob Marley, or go to the movies every day ... or stay up all night writing code ... or play virtual reality video games ....... or travel the world, the solar system.... ..... the galaxy. Ya know.. just be Normal. 
&nbsp;
... Of course, history shows us that societies usually don't work out that simply. Sometimes, people may even be offended by your version of 'freedom'... as has been the case with recreational drug users, just to give an example... or people being naked in public..... ........ or people hunting animals for food. Sometimes, people have different versions of freedom altogether.
&nbsp;
At the heart of all this is scarcity, and ego. Not even self-proclaimed freedom fighters are immune to this disease, which is probably why you'd never catch me dead at a Gay Rights rally ... or wearing Greenpeace, PETA stickers ... even though I'm an LGBT vegetarian.
&nbsp;
My first dose of politics and philosophy would no doubt have been taken at the age of 9 in Germany, when my dad talked to me about how slaughterhouses worked. Since then, I've kinda earned a reputation for being an animal lover on my primary school playgrounds. Animal rights became my thing..
&nbsp;
Then again, as I grew older and witnessed news coverage of the war in the middle east, the refugee crisis, etc. it became apparent that there's little hope to be found in the animal rights movement, considering how awfully we already treat members of our own species. Sometimes we even treat people worse than we treat animals. Try talking to somebody about Saving the Whales. Then try talking to them about Saving the Refugees...
&nbsp;
The reason we cannot save all refugees is because there's scarcity in Europe, and a war of Egos in the middle east.. and the reason we cannot save all whales is because, some people eat them. They use them as a source of chemical energy.. to sustain their own bodies.
&nbsp;
Scarcity even explains racism, homophobia, xenophobia, etc. After all, Trump and Brexit are all a byproduct of a new underclass (i.e. The Precariat) that is facing economic uncertainty amidst globalization, automation, job loss.. lower benefits, lower wages, etc. . and so they find a way to lash out their frustrations at the world. 
&nbsp;
Might also have something to do with the fact that politicians were quick to rally up behind Gay Marriage and Transgender anti-discrimination laws, without addressing more urgent issues such as wealth inequality, poverty, homelessness, etc... all of which are issues that actually affect LGBT and ethnic minorities more often than the rest. I'd take Basic Income, affordable housing, affordable health care.. over gay marriage, any day. Growing up with non-accepting parents, my biggest issue was by far was not having enough money, and not having a place I could call my own .... not 'sexism, racism, etc'. People in New Zealand have actually treated me pretty decently.
&nbsp;
Maybe this is why gays and trans have received so much hate as of lately. The ones who get the most attention are often rich college kids who dye their hair and wear stickers and start flame wars on social media, not because they really care about the disadvantaged... but because, hey.. Identity Politics is fun. Feeding the homeless is not.
&nbsp;
This gives us all a bad image... unfortunately.
&nbsp;
Anywhoo. In conclusion, Violence, protests, whining, flaming.. won't really solve this problem.
&nbsp;
Our only hope is technology, science.. and reason. Hell .. technology might even bring us global vegetarianism and animal rights, that is .. if we can create artificial lab-grown meat that is healthier, cheaper and tastier than the real thing. 
&nbsp;
If there's a problem, throw technology at it. That's kinda what ZeroNet is about, too. Don't join political parties, don't waste your breath.. don't try too hard to argue with people and convince them ... and for god's sakes, don't throw your life away fighting pointless wars. 
&nbsp;
Be who you wanna be, don't let people tell you how to live your life, and vice versa. The right to life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness. If there's a universal morality, that would have to be it.

