The problem with search engines on ZeroNet right now is that they rely almost entirely on human input in order to build up a proper database. You don't have the luxury of using web crawlers in order to search for content, because content needs to be downloaded onto a disk in order to be read, including databases.. unless you're using a ZeroNet proxy. They also tend to be biased toward sites that the creator likes.
&nbsp;
I suppose the only way to beat this problem would be to create a ZeroNet python plugin (call it CrawlerBot) that automatically queries every single .db file of every single zite you've downloaded simply looking for links with http://127.0.0.1:43110/*
&nbsp;
It would then update that database universally across all ZeroNet clients, and could be queried by any zite. Duplicates are simply ignored, but new links are added.

